    "19075575": {
      "title": "Cellular RNA-dependent RNA polymerase involved in posttranscriptional gene silencing has two distinct activity modes",
      "abstract": "Abstract Recent genetic data suggest that proteins homologous to a plant RNA-dependent RNA polymerase (RdRP) play a central role in posttranscriptional gene silencing (PTGS) in many organisms. We show here that purified recombinant protein QDE-1, a genetic component of PTGS (\"quelling\") in the fungus Neurospora crassa , possesses RNA polymerase activity in vitro. The full-length enzyme and its enzymatically active C-terminal fragment perform two different reactions on single-stranded RNA templates, synthesizing either extensive RNA chains that form template-length duplexes or ∼9–21-mer complementary RNA oligonucleotides scattered along the entire template. QDE-1 supports both de novo and primer-dependent initiation mechanisms. These results suggest that several distinct activities of cell-encoded RdRPs can be employed for efficient PTGS in vivo."
    }
  },
